{% extends 'extractors/_meta/extractor.j2' %}

{% block instructions %}
Read the source. Identify the **citations** for this source — list of citations; each is one of variants {paper|preprint, book, article, report} — see schema.

Use ONLY content the source supports. When the source is silent on a
field, set it to null (where the schema permits null). Never invent.

### CRITICAL — never fill metadata from priors

Many sources reference works **generically** ("a paper from McKinsey",
"the survey paper linked in the slides", "researchers published a
HyDE paper", "a 2022 NeurIPS paper popularized chain-of-thought").
You MAY know the canonical author list, exact title, year, venue,
DOI, or URL from training. **Do not write those fields.**

Rules:

- A field is supported ONLY if the source's prose names it (or the
  source displays it in a slide/quote that the converter captured
  verbatim). A URL embedded in a slide image counts as
  source-supported only if the converter transcribed it.
- For every emitted citation, the ``source_quote`` MUST be the
  verbatim passage in which the source identifies the work. If the
  passage is "a paper from McKinsey", that's all you have:
  ``title``, ``authors``, ``year``, ``venue``, ``doi``, ``url``
  must all be ``null``.
- Inferring an arXiv id or full author list from a URL slug counts
  as fabrication. Do not do it.
- If you can name a work but the source supports almost nothing
  about it, prefer dropping the citation entirely over emitting a
  near-empty stub.

The schema enforces shape; load it implicitly via ``loom output init`` and
fill the required fields below. Refer to the on-disk schema at
``templates/extractors/citations/schema.yaml`` for the exact field set,
required keys, and any per-variant rules.
{% endblock %}

{% block builder_calls %}

    {{ vars.loom_sh }} output add {{ run.workdir }} --task {{ task.id }} \
        --set citations.<i>.<key>='<value>' [--set ...]

Repeat for each item / field group the schema requires. Indices are
0-based. For string|null fields, pass ``null`` to leave unset.
{% endblock %}
